'''Gianfranco Cimmino''' (12 March 1908 – 30 May 1989) was an Italian [[mathematician]], working [[mathematical analysis]], [[numerical analysis]], and [[Elliptic partial differential equation|theory of elliptic partial differential equations]]: he is known for being the first mathematician generalizing in a [[weak formulation|weak sense]] the notion of boundary value in a [[boundary value problem]],<ref>{{harv|Pini|1991|p=120}}, {{harv|Scorza Dragoni|1991|pp=63–64}} and {{harv|Sbordone|2008|p=8}}.</ref><ref>See also {{harv|Miranda|1955}} and its revised and translated second edition {{harv|Miranda|1970}}.</ref> and for doing an influential work in numerical analysis.<ref>{{harv|Benzi|2005}}.</ref>
