'''Some Remarks on Logical Form'''<ref>http://www.uni.edu/boedeker/logicalform.pdf</ref> ({{lang-de|Bemerkungen über logische Form}}) was the only academic paper ever published by [[Ludwig Wittgenstein]], and contained Wittgenstein's thinking on [[logic]] and the [[Wittgenstein's philosophy of mathematics|philosophy of mathematics]] immediately before the rupture that divided the early Wittgenstein of the [[Tractatus Logico-Philosophicus]] from the later Wittgenstein.<ref>{{cite journal | url = http://www.springerlink.com/content/n822h6j1782713v1/ | doi=10.1007/BF00485322 | volume=56 | title=Some remarks on (Wittgensteinian) logical form | year=1983 | journal=Synthese | pages=155–170 | last1 = Hintikka | first1 = Jaakko | last2 = Hintikka | first2 = Merrill B.}}</ref> The approach to [[logical form]] in the paper reflected [[Frank P. Ramsey]]'s critique of Wittgenstein's account in the Tractatus, and has been analyzed by [[G.E.M. Anscombe]] and [[Jaakko Hintikka]], among others.<ref>{{cite journal | url = http://www.springerlink.com/content/n822h6j1782713v1/ | doi=10.1007/BF00485322 | volume=56 | title=Some remarks on (Wittgensteinian) logical form | year=1983 | journal=Synthese | pages=155–170 | last1 = Hintikka | first1 = Jaakko | last2 = Hintikka | first2 = Merrill B.}}</ref>
