'''Vyjayanthi Chari''' (born 1958)<ref>Birth year from [http://www.isni.org/isni/0000000115646013 ISNI authority control file], accessed 2018-11-26.</ref> is an Indian–American professor of mathematics at the [[University of California, Riverside]], known for her research in [[representation theory]] and [[quantum algebra]].<ref name="profile">{{citation|url=http://mathdept.ucr.edu/faculty/chari.html|title=Faculty profile|publisher=Department of Mathematics, University of California, Riverside|accessdate=2015-11-17}}.</ref>
Chari has a bachelor's, master's, and doctoral degree from the [[University of Mumbai]].<ref name="profile"/> Her dissertation was supervised by [[Rajagopalan Parthasarathy]].<ref>{{mathgenealogy|id=49988}}</ref>
With Andrew N. Pressley, she is the author of the book ''A Guide to Quantum Groups'' (Cambridge University Press, 1994).<ref>Review of ''A Guide to Quantum Groups'' by Tomasz Brzeziński (1995), {{MR|1300632}}.</ref>
In 2015 she was elected as a [[fellow]] of the [[American Mathematical Society]].<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.ams.org/profession/ams-fellows/new-fellows|title=2016 Class of the Fellows of the AMS|publisher=[[American Mathematical Society]]|accessdate=2015-11-17}}.</ref>
